[{"id":"VR105608","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Based on the pedigree in Figure 1, which of the following best explains the observed pattern of inheritance?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR105608_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<p><img alt=\"The figure presents a pedigree of an inherited trait. Three generations are shown and are given the Roman numerals, from top to bottom, 1, 2, and 3. Each individual within a generation is also numbered with digits such that the left most individual in the first generation, generation 1, is called 1 1, the second individual in the first generation is called 1 2, and so on. The first generation of the pedigree consists of the following four individuals: 1 1 an unaffected male, 1 2 an unaffected female, 1 3 an affected male, and 1 4 a second unaffected female. Unaffected male 1 1 and unaffected female 1 2 produce second generation individuals 2 1 an unaffected male and 2 2 an affected female. Affected male 1 3 and unaffected female 1 4 produce second generation individuals 2 3 an unaffected male, 2 4 an affected female, and 2 5 another unaffected male. Affected female 2 2 and unaffected male 2 3 produce third generation individuals 3 1 an affected female and 3 2 an unaffected female. Unaffected male 2 5 and an unaffected female 2 6 produce third generation individuals 3 3 an unaffected male and 3 4 an affected male.\" class=\"text-left\" height=\"337\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR105608.g04.png\" width=\"300\" /></p>\n\n<p class=\"passage_para\">Figure 1. Pedigree of an inherited trait</p>\n"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The trait is autosomal dominant, because the cross between individuals <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1 3\"><math alttext=\"1 3\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>I-3</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1 4\"><math alttext=\"1 4\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>I-4</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> produced an affected offspring.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The trait is autosomal recessive, because the cross between individuals <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1 1\"><math alttext=\"1 1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>I-1</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1 2\"><math alttext=\"1 2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>I-2</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> produced an affected offspring.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The trait is sex-linked dominant, because the cross between individuals <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 5\"><math alttext=\"2 5\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>II-5</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 6\"><math alttext=\"2 6\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>II-6</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> produced an affected male.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The trait is sex-linked recessive, because the cross between individuals <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 2\"><math alttext=\"2 2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>II-2</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 3\"><math alttext=\"2 3\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>II-3</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> produced an affected female.</p>"],"answer":1}]